    "description": "There is no better way to make this beautiful weather in Mumbai more exciting, than to come together and discuss amazing ideas, learn something new, meet amazing people and in turn grow our community.\n\nWith that said, Mumbai Women Coders is back again with an exciting meetup in the month of July. The meetup is never possible without someone igniting and sharing their idea, so here we announce the speakers and there topics\n\n1. Sayalee Pote : CoreML in iOS\n\nTalk will start with a very brief explanation of what machine learning actually is.This will be followed by an introduction to CoreML, which is Apple\u2019s Machine Learning framework for iOS. This is will be a detailed explanation of functioning of CoreML, where does CoreML fit in the iOS App structure and various libraries in CoreML (Vision, Natural Language Processing, GameplayKit). The talk will proceed to show what it takes to integrate CoreML in your iOS app. This includes system setup and various ways in which you can feed a trained model to the iOS app to work with.\n\n2. Arwa Lokhandwala : Lets make your javascript journey easy\n\nThis talk aims at giving you some very handy tips and few coding practices to make your javascript programming fun and interesting. At the same time it would help you to improve your code quality.\n\n3. Avinash : Painless refactoring with selectors\n\nSelectors are the way of computing derived data from redux stores.\n\n4. Interactive session with Attendees : How did you get started with coding?\n\nIts an interactive session, where we would like you to share what is the best coding practice that helped you, don't worry if you are beginners, share your coding ideas so that we can all get better!!\n\nRequirement : As our meetup is open to all kinds of tech, please come with an open mind :)",
